Detailed Description

BtDeviceListIterator is used to iterate a BtDeviceList in the normal order. Dereferencing the iterator returns pointers or references to objects. So these objects can be changed through this iterator.

iterator dereference operator

BtDeviceListIterator BtDeviceListIterator::operator++ (  int   ) 
 

iterator increment operator (postfix)

operator++ is the postfix incrment operator and is used to move the current position that the iterator is representing in a BtDeviceList forward to the next position in the list.

Returns:
A BtDeviceListIterator that is representing the iterator before advancing. The iterator itself is either the next position in the BtDeviceList or the past-the-end iterator.

iterator decrement iterator (postfix)
